examples.en: The stew smelled delicious.
This car smells like mold.
The shirt smelled of perfume.
I think I smell gas.
Can't you smell the profits?
I could smell dinner cooking.
Dogs have a keen sense of smell.
Her hair smelled of apple blossoms.
The water was dirty and smelled yucky.
She leaned over and smelled the flowers.
I have a cold right now so I can't smell.
The antis smelled victory after a long battle.
She smelled the different perfumes at the store.
I can't smell anything because I'm so stuffed up.
The old dog snorted like a pig when it smelled food.
Neighbours raised the alarm when they smelled smoke.
Carrie smelled coffee and her eyes opened reluctantly.
The room smelled to high heaven (=had a very bad smell).
Miller had smelled trouble the moment she said who she was.
Our mouths filled with saliva when we smelled the delicious dinner.
We were ravenous after our canoe paddling, and the chili bubbling over the campfire smelled heavenly.
